The President met with his National Security Council to discuss the status of the campaign against ISIL. They reviewed the political and security situation in Iraq and Syria and discussed ongoing efforts to train and equip Iraqi ground forces. They also talked about supporting the moderate Syrian opposition and coordinating with regional partners. Various members of the National Security Council were present at the meeting, including the Vice President, Secretary of State, Secretary of Defense, Secretary of Homeland Security, and Director of the Central Intelligence Agency.